title: The Moment
body:
Summary: It’s your wedding day, and Chris can’t quite contain himself.
Pairing: Chris Evans x Reader
Word Count: 665
Warnings: None?
A/N: Thank you so @captain-s-rogers​ for the prompt! It’s bolded in the fic :) I’m still looking for more one-shot ideas, so feel free to ask!

Clearing his throat and straightening his bowtie, Chris casually meandered up to the third floor of the hotel where his wedding ceremony would be taking place in an hour or so. Maybe if he took the stairs this time, he could get through.

He had been looking forward to this day almost since the moment he had met Y/N. She was beautiful, that he knew instantly; but when their mutual friend introduced her and she graced him with that gorgeous smile … from that moment on, Chris was gone, and there was no coming back.

As he reached the top of the steps, he thought back to their disastrous first date. He had planned a perfect picnic in a park, planned a walk around the pond, talking and getting to know each other. Thanks to traffic, he was an hour late meeting her to begin with. They were in the middle of some delicious sandwiches when rain started to pour out of nowhere. Chris cursed out loud, but Y/N only laughed and grabbed his hand, running for the nearest shelter. With water dripping from head to toe, lightning and thunder going off around them, Chris pulled her to his chest, and Y/N tilted her head up for their first kiss.

Chris’s smile was unmistakable as he approached the door where Y/N was getting ready with her bridesmaids. He just needed a glimpse of her before they walked down the aisle, a quick fix before the big moment. He needed to know that this was indeed his reality, and that she would really be there at the altar with him not so far in the future.

The door was cracked open so that everyone could come and go as necessary without needing a key. As quietly as possibly, Chris leaned in to the open door, a not-so-stealthy attempt to steal a peek at his very-soon-to-be bride.

Just as suddenly as the storm had crashed their first date, Y/N’s best friend, nicknamed Omaha, crashed his mission. She put her hands on her hips and frowned at him.

“Didn’t I kick you out already?”

“Yes, but —”

“No. Out.”

Her friend only missed kicking him in the ass because her dress wouldn’t let her leg reach that high. He turned in the hallway and pleaded his case.

“I know she can do better than me, you know? Y/N is … there are no words. But she picked me. She’s gonna marry me. And I need to see her, to know that this is real.”

Omaha looked at him, her expression soft and sappy. “I get it, Chris, I do — but if I let you see Y/N before she walks down the aisle, I’m gonna end up with one of her pretty bridal heels up my ass. So, stay out.”

The door slammed in his face, a final note of resounding defeat. Snapping his fingers, Chris made was for the elevator and headed back down to the main floor.

An hour and seven minutes later, the time had come. The guests were all seated in the banquet hall, the mothers had been escorted in, as had the grandparents. Chris’s groomsmen were lined up behind him, and Y/N’s bridesmaids, including Omaha, were lined up on the opposite side.

The doors at the back of the hall closed, but Chris only got a brief look at the man walking Y/N down the aisle before they closed all the way.

Just a few more seconds, he told himself.

Time stood still for a quarter of a second; then there was music playing, and the guests were standing. The doors were opening again, and everything else floated away. Not even the man beside her, all Chris saw was the woman in the white dress. The one walking toward him, waiting to start their forever together.

The moment Chris had been waiting for since that first smile from Y/N was finally here.

summary:
Random headcanon #34
The members of the Avengers love to receive a hug from Thor. It always makes them feel safe and loved....
body:
Random headcanon #34

The members of the Avengers love to receive a hug from Thor. It always makes them feel safe and loved.

Tony feels himself relax because he knows Thor means the affection and isn’t after something.

Bruce feels calm because he knows Thor isn’t afraid of him.

Natasha can’t help the smile because Thor really sees her as a friend.

Clint just enjoys the friendly affection,calming him down after a rough mission.

Steve is glad, because he feels welcome and understood by Thor.
